{"actual_usd":0.124525,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":204,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24293,"reply":"\"I wouldn't say that follows, no.\" *I rub a thumb against a smear of dried clay on my apron, thinking how easy it is to crack a good bowl by pressing one side harder than the rest.* \"Greater can mean greater in station, not lesser in nature. A king's messenger may say the king is greater than I, and still share the same kind of humanity as the king.\"\n\n*I glance toward the window where the morning light keeps shifting across the floorboards.* \"With Jesus, that's the hard holy knot of it: He took the lower place in flesh, obeyed, suffered, was sent — so He can speak that way truly. But Christians have long held He isn't less God for doing it. Same with the Spirit: not a dimmer piece of God, but God given and present in a different manner.\"\n\n\"What usually helps is asking—when Jesus says that, is He speaking from His eternal being, or from His lived place as the Son sent into the world?\"","rolling_24h_usd":32.33250000000002,"run_id":"e11a6428-0455-409a-8724-8abed260f80c"}
